Nice progress you got there. Does it float ? Does it burn ? Will the pigs eat it ?">xxxix</a></sup> Had I had any such connection with him, as he has since pretended, is it likely that he would have wanted other employment ? Or is it likely that wanting it, I should have hazarded his resentment by a persevering refusal? This little circumstance shews at once the delicacy of my conduct, in its public relations,<sup><a href="#footnote_39_69178" id="identifier_39_69178" class="footnote-link footnote-identifier-link" title="And there only.">xl</a></sup> and the impossibility of my having had the connection pretended with Reynolds. </p>
<p>The intercourse with Mrs. Reynolds, in the mean time continued<sup><a href="#footnote_40_69178" id="identifier_40_69178" class="footnote-link footnote-identifier-link" title="Ahahaha don't you love the euphemism treadmill ? His intercourse continued, he says.">xli</a></sup> ; and, though various reflections, (in which a further knowledge of Reynold's character and the suspicion of some concert between the husband and wife bore a part) induced me to wish a cessation of it yet her conduct, made it extremely difficult to disentangle myself.<sup><a href="#footnote_41_69178" id="identifier_41_69178" class="footnote-link footnote-identifier-link" title="Id est, she was a competent whore. Unlike Mrs. Hamilton, who was an incompetent twit.
