						<p>Yeah, what about dat xlii footnote.</p>
<p>Apparently it hasn't yet occured to anyone ~this generation~ that being female puts some technical requirements on the head of the subject, you can't just "be" a woman, you gotta work it, there's skill involved, and knowledge, and practice. The fundamental characteristic of an acultural population (which ipso facto is <em>subhuman</em>), each new generation has to discover the entire world by itself, can't possibly refer to previous experience.</p>
<p>And then they wonder why they're fat and depressed. Apparently it's inconceivable that if you imagine yourself ontologically sufficient, as if somehow your mere presence is going to sexually satisfy, then therefore you <em>lose</em> something thereby, and that something looks very much like "everything".</p>
<p>Yes, I get it, they're lazy, stupid and fat because the boys are weird and don't push them. Sure. The form this "don't push them" takes is in the delirious belief that women are somehow objectively, ontologically sufficient. They aren't. They couldn't be. </p>
<p><a href=http://trilema.com/2013/back-to-work-whore/ >Back to work</a>.</p>
						</li>

